2w0.title: Uncountability
2w0.clickbait: Some infinities are bigger than others. Uncountable infinities are larger than countable infinities.
2w0.text:
Sizes of infinity fall into two broad classes: *countable* infinities, and *uncountable* infinities.

A set $S$ is *uncountable* if it is not [6f8 countable].

2w1.clickbait: Not all infinities are created equal.  The infinity of real numbers is infinitely larger than the infinity of counting numbers.

summaries.Summary:
[3jz Collections of things] which are the same [4w5 size] as or smaller than the collection of all [-45h natural numbers] are called *countable*, while larger collections (like the set of all [-4bc real numbers]) are called *uncountable*.

All uncountable collections (and some countable collections) are [infinity infinite]. There is a meaningful and [5ss well-defined] way to compare the sizes of different infinite collections of things, and some infinite collections are larger than others.
